Description: Masinios was so absorbed in future machinery and could not get enough that he changed his name to Masinios. Because of this, his previous name was forever buried in the darkness of history, never to be known. However, the Masinios Spear is made by the recipe he designed before his renaming, so his name can be traced through the magical power left in the recipe. Since Masinios is not such a popular person from the past, no one has tried so far.
Name: Masinios Spear

After studying the returned weapons, Owynia Dilben sought the help of the Bullet Marker Master to produce new copies of the equipment. Curiously, however, until they gain a proper owner, the newly-created weapons seem to disappear and reappear at random times.
Name: Primus Zvaigzde Spear

Description: Long ago, a goddess suggested the crafting of objects to the other goddesses. Most of the goddesses that heeded their colleague's suggestion mainly did so out of amusement, but the goddess that suggested it meant to leave the objects containing the divine powers of the goddesses in the world for the generations to come. One of those arrangements are these gloves
Name: Ogva Gloves

Description: It is uncertain if whether the Goddess' Ancient Garden where these gloves were crafted indicates the same location as the Goddess' Ancient Garden known today. Whatever the location may be, the gloves were certainly made in the Goddess' Ancient Garden.
Name: Ogva Leather Gloves

Description: Some believe that there is an all powerful piece of equipment that contains extreme amounts of divine power based on the fact that Ogva equipment is completed by the goddesses' divine power and spend their lives trying to find it. Of course, all such efforts resulted in failure and it is unknown if there actually is such a piece of equipment. However, those searches did result in the discovery of previously unknown equipment such as these gloves.
Name: Ogva Chain Gloves

Description: There have been attempts to control plants with other plants since Medzio Diena. These pieces of equipment are one of the successfully applied cases of those attempts.
Name: Partis Gloves

Description: The effort of waiting for the moment a fern blooms in a special place where noone can see is required to craft these gloves. The patience and concentration is rewarded by the gloves enhancing the accuracy of the wearer.
Name: Partis Leather Gloves

Description: The individual rings that comprise these gloves have been crafted through the application of magical powers symbolized by fern buds. Magical equipment with this sort of power may not be craftable if the vegetation abnormality disappears one day.
Name: Partis Ring Gloves

Description: There was a time when Divdirbys master Tesla used to roam the kingdom. Some pieces of magic equipment have tales of his travels. People usually accept such legends even though it is uncertain how the sculptor priest Tesla influenced the crafting of these gloves.
Name: Sirdgela Gloves

Description: The reason Sirdgela equipment has more diverse and mystical stories than other magical equipment may be influenced by the unique environment of being a Thorn Forest. However, if that is the case, it means that all the stories are from after Medzio Diena making them works of fiction.
Name: Sirdgela Leather Gloves

Description: It is said that many wild animals existed in Sirdgela even before the increase of monsters after Medzio Diena. These gloves are said to have existed since then.
Name: Sirdgela Scale Gloves

Description: Philis Gloves are said to have had more magic before Medzio Diena. The reasons behind the weakening of magic after the collapse of the 3 layer castle wall on Medzio Diena remains unknown.
Name: Philis Gloves

Description: The regulation issued uniforms of the guards of the 3 layer castle wall were produced in various forms according to their needs. These gloves were produced with ordinary siege warfare in mind.
Name: Philis Leather Gloves

Description: It was only issued to the outer wall guards during the early years of the kingdom. It was thought to be useful under the assumption that the outer wall was taken. It was later issued to all 3 walls as tactics and weapons of siege warfare changed.
Name: Philis Scale Gloves

Description: Although it is a strange phenomenon, the activities of mages and production of magical items is relatively active in the Allerno Barony when compared to other fiefs. This phenomena has increased dramatically after Medzio Diena and these gloves have appeared in such circumstances.
Name: Allerno Gloves

Description: Whatever the reason behind the sudden appearance of items may be, they are actively gathering and issuing such items to men in Allerno barony. This may be the reason behind mounting conflicts between the residents and soldiers in the region.
Name: Allerno Leather Gloves

Description: The current lord of Allerno has hired mages and craftsmen in order to further enhance the equipment that already has strong defensive powers. It is said that such moves are hiding other reasons.
Name: Allerno Plate Gauntlets

Description: There are cases of divine power residing in items that had been carried by priests for a long time. Perelin gloves were crafted as a successful result of trying to have these happenings occur reliably when needed.
Name: Perelin Gloves

Description: There are increased chances of items becoming Perelin items in the case of making pilgrims perform various tasks whilst wearing the equipment such as these gloves. However, it cannot be seen as a precise recipe as the exact moment that they receive divine power is unknown.
Name: Perelin Leather Gloves

Description: Although it may seem obvious, these Perelin gloves appear frequently on Paladins.
Name: Perelin Plate Gauntlets

Description: Many mages have crafted numerous magical items in the mage tower since Agailla Flurry's death. Most of the creators are anonymous despite several of the items still being used to this day. These are designated as Turn equipment.
Name: Turn Gloves

Description: There was a time when the mages of the Mage Tower after Flurry's death isolated themselves from the world and focused on their experiments and research. Although there were many whimsical inventions during that time, the only partially practical inventions that remain are these Turn gloves.
Name: Turn Leather Gloves

Description: Some Turn equipment has been reinforced or applied in various ways while being used outside of the Mage Tower. The first known case of such enhancements are these gloves.
Name: Turn Plate Gauntlets

Description: The Druid Master from Shaton and tried to make the region safer after Medzio Diena by providing or helping the crafting of equipment. There are cases in which non-combatant farmers have received help from these gloves.
Name: Shaton Gloves

Description: Shaton equipment provides diverse amenities for the livelihood of the locals even if they do not fight monsters. Even farmers and lumberjacks need to be accurate.
Name: Shaton Leather Gloves

Description: The Druid Master also freely gave help to the nobles of the Shaton region. As a result, the nobility of Shaton was able to increase their survivability when combating monsters.
Name: Shaton Plate Gauntlets

Description: Many people have found various means to donate to the Tyla Monastery which is a historic religious facility. Those donations became the foundations to the emergence to magical equipment unique to the Tyla Monastery.

Name: Ogva Leather Boots

Description: We cannot know which powers were given to the various pieces of equipment by certain goddesses long ago in the Goddess' Ancient Garden. However, we can make assumptions. These boots most likely have the divine power of Zemyna.
Name: Ogva Chain Boots

Description: It is a difficult task to magically apply the self protection substances of ferns to weapons after Medzio Diena. The goddesses must be thanked for the fact that those efforts succeeded.
Name: Partis Boots

Description: The ritual of watching a fern bloom before Medzio Diena was thought to be a custom for wish fulfillment or good luck, but just like all life has changed afterwards, is now a method of applying magic to protective equipment such as this.
Name: Partis Leather Boots

Description: All vegetation that saw explosive growth after Medzio Diena possess some degree of life and energy absorption. To apply this ability to equipment and allow it to absorb energy from the earth is a very difficult task.
Name: Partis Ring Boots

Description: There is a legend of Tesla crafting these boots after being pricked by a thorn in the foot whilst passing Sirdgela Forest. Whether the forest was filled with thorns or if Tesla really crafted the boots after such an experience is not important. Nobody has gone to ask Tesla even though he is alive and well.
Name: Sirdgela Boots

Description: According to legend, there were many soldiers going missing in or near Sirdgela, and these boots were crafted by the families and friends looking for their lost ones.
Name: Sirdgela Leather Boots

Description: Although this is only one of the many theories that surrounds Sirdgela equipment, it is said that these boots have been traditionally crafted in the Sirdgela region to traverse rough terrain.
Name: Sirdgela Scale Boots

Description: Philis equipment is characterized by it's ability to provide it's wearers with pleasantness in closed environments.
Name: Philis Boots

Description: The regulation issued uniforms of the guards of the 3 layer castle wall were produced in various forms according to their needs. These boots were produced with ordinary siege warfare in mind.
Name: Philis Leather Boots

Description: It is the most useful equipment with magical properties not only all castle guards including those on the 3 layers. It has existed as a favorite of many guards for a long time.
Name: Philis Scale Boots

Description: The increase in magical items in the Allerno barony is hard to explain especially when it has always been an agricultural region. Whatever the reason may be, the people fighting in the region can attribute these boots to that phenomenon.
Name: Allerno Boots

Description: It is certain that the Allerno region is being magically influenced from the outside. Although it may not be an impressive amount, the fact still stands that these boots regardless of their performance show new methods of magic infusion.
Name: Allerno Leather Boots

Description: If the lord of Allerno did not simply hire the mages and craftsmen to enhance the magical equipment, there is a chance that his goal may be connected to why such items are suddenly appearing.
Name: Allerno Plate Greaves

Description: There are cases in which the divine power of goddesses indwells and shows new powers in trivial items that poor pilgrims were carrying on their pilgrimage. Equipment with the name Perelin are such items.
Name: Perelin Boots

Description: The effects of Perelin items do not disappear even if given to other people after realizing that they have become Perelin items during the pilgrimage. There is no firm principle behind the creation of Perelin items even though pilgrims that have had a piece of equipment turn into Perelin items before usually are able to have more.
Name: Perelin Leather Boots

Description: Perelin items do not always appear on priests. There are numerous cases in which Perelin gloves have appeared on warrior type believers.
Name: Perelin Plate Greaves

Description: Turn equipment have nothing more in common than the fact that they have their origins in the Mage tower. They are simply named as such due to the need to indicate equipment from the tower after Flurry.
Name: Turn Boots

Description: According to some, Turn equipment may have had better power in the beginning. However, there are no remaining items or recipes due to the reclusive nature of mages. Most of the equipment left has about the same amount of magic as these boots.
Name: Turn Leather Boots

Description: There was a time where metallic equipment was not crafted because of the many experiments conducted by mages after Flurry's death. Therefore, the existing metallic Turn equipment may have originated from mages but have been completed by anonymous contributors outside of the Mage Tower.
Name: Turn Plate Greaves

Description: The Druid Master is sending several of her disciples to Shaton to perform various tasks not only out of the love of her hometown but also becuase it is related to her Nature Restoration Plan. The local residents are imitating a few of the simple magic equipment that are used to keep the disciples safe.
Name: Shaton Boots

Description: Some settlers from the Shaton region have disappeared with the equipment. It is unclear if they made a run for it after obtaining equipment or have fallen victim to monsters. Both are equally as likely to have happened. The fact that many of those that have disappeared are people that have obtained boots suggests a certain possibility.
Name: Shaton Leather Boots

Description: The Druid Master also freely gave help to the nobles of the Shaton region. As a result, the nobility of Shaton was able to increase their survivability when combating monsters.
Name: Shaton Plate Greaves

Description: Some of the Tyla Monastery equipment was improved with the consent of the original donor. Many people could receive the benefits of such equipment because the Tyla Monastery does not monopolize these items.

Description: Once used as an alliance uniform in days of economic prosperity, today it is worn for slightly  different purposes.
Name: Primus Alpra Boots

Description: A garment said to have originated from the East. Despite being made of leather, it is still a fairly breathable piece.
Name: Primus Eastern Leather Boots

Description: As a piece of equipment made from layers of iron plate, it was initially specialized to resist arrow attacks. These days, however, it has evolved to protect against all types of attacks equally.
Name: Primus Pangle Plate Greaves

Description: A uniform worn by the kingdom's wizard combatants. Being able to wear this piece was considered a big honor in those days.
Name: Primus Warmage Boots

Description: A uniform worn by the kingdom's rangers. In those days, rangers were treated with the same reverence as knights.
Name: Primus Eaglestar Leather Boots

Description: The official uniform of the kingdom's knight order.
Name: Primus Nyx Knight Greaves

Description: Marone equipment originated from a religious order. In year 215 of the Kingdom, clerics began to divide into different orders, each developing their own style of equipment. Over time, these religious equipment items became more often used by those not related to an order.
Name: Primus Marone Boots

Description: Prakeh equipment remains as a heritage from the era of King Chaspael. The lack of beauty in each item reflects the hardship of living in those times.
Name: Primus Prakeh Boots

Description: Razna equipment is named after a species of monster currently extinct. According to legends, the last few were isolated in a special location, as they were considered dangerous by demons and goddesses alike. The association between this monster and the equipment it's named after remains a mystery.
Name: Primus Razna Leather Boots

Description: Keyarc equipment was once once amongst the most popular items made by the Kedoran Alliance. After Medzio Diena, the Alliance is once again selling this equipment, although it is unsure how much profit it can yield given that they are now being produced by other organizations as well.
Name: Primus Keyarc Leather Boots

Description: Barghar equipment was born of an attempt to reproduce Ruklys' legendary magic resistance equipment. It may not be as effective as Ruklys', but it is fairly useful nonetheless.
Name: Primus Barghar Plate Boots

Description: The first person to ever wear this equipment was Geoffrey Parecius, grandfather of current Lancer Master Noer Parecius. He is said to have been close to the Black family, possessing a strong interest in equipment making himself as well.
Name: Primus Suurit Plate Boots

Description: A strong piece of armor made with high-quality fabrics and magic fur. Very wearable and warm.
Name: Primus Kalinis Boots

Description: A strong piece of armor made from an extremely rare type of white leather.
Name: Primus Albinosas Leather Boots

Description: A strong piece of armor made of a foreign metal name titanium. It is as heavy as it is tough.
Name: Primus Tajtanas Greaves

Description: A strong piece of armor made of an exquisite golden fabric. Rumor has it this armor was worn by the nobility in faraway nations.
Name: Primus Oksinis Boots

Description: A strong piece of armor made of monster leather and bones. Rumor has it warriors from faraway countries adorned their armor with large bones to represent their skill.
Name: Primus Kaulas Leather Boots

Description: A strong piece of armor worn by the royal knights of a faraway nation. It contains pure gold.
Name: Primus Krisius Greaves

Description: Boots made from the beaks of eagles.
Name: Primus Irellis Boots

Description: Boots made from a special ivy. They are environmentally friendly.
Name: Primus Jevenellis Leather Boots

Description: It is said that this equipment was named after Demon Lord "Ausura" who was created by Gesti herself, but it seems this is just mere coincidence. There is no reason that Man would praise the name of the Demon. And for Ausura this is still an ill news since even maybe Ausura is a Demon Lord but still, there are many superiors still ahead.
Name: Ausura Greaves

Description: No one knows for sure if there are other dragons besides Boruta and Velcoffer roaming our world, but the possibility is there. Especially after Medzio Diena, these creatures have had more opportunities than ever to escape their confinement.

Name: Sirdgela Pants

Name: Philis Pants

Description: Unlike other pieces of Philis equipment, this piece did not exist before Medzio Diena. It was recently infused with magical properties out of necessity.
Name: Philis Leather Pants

An interesting theory that is brought up even now is that those guards may have been able to stop the catastrophic growth of vegetation from the capital which is now in ruins.
Name: Philis Scale Pants

Description: Once used as an alliance uniform in days of economic prosperity, today it is worn for slightly  different purposes.
Name: Primus Alpra Pants

Description: A garment said to have originated from the East. Despite being made of leather, it is still a fairly breathable piece.
Name: Primus Eastern Leather Pants

Description: As a piece of equipment made from layers of iron plate, it was initially specialized to resist arrow attacks. These days, however, it has evolved to protect against all types of attacks equally.
Name: Primus Pangle Plate Leggings

Description: A uniform worn by the kingdom's wizard combatants. Being able to wear this piece was considered a big honor in those days.
Name: Primus Warmage Pants

Description: A uniform worn by the kingdom's rangers. In those days, rangers were treated with the same reverence as knights.
Name: Primus Eaglestar Leather Pants

Description: The official uniform of the kingdom's knight order.
Name: Primus Nyx Knight Pants

Description: Marone equipment originated from a religious order. In year 215 of the Kingdom, clerics began to divide into different orders, each developing their own style of equipment. Over time, these religious equipment items became more often used by those not related to an order.
Name: Primus Marone Pants

Description: Prakeh equipment remains as a heritage from the era of King Chaspael. The lack of beauty in each item reflects the hardship of living in those times.
Name: Primus Prakeh Pants

Description: Razna equipment is named after a species of monster currently extinct. According to legends, the last few were isolated in a special location, as they were considered dangerous by demons and goddesses alike. The association between this monster and the equipment it's named after remains a mystery.
Name: Primus Razna Leather Pants

Description: Keyarc equipment was once once amongst the most popular items made by the Kedoran Alliance. After Medzio Diena, the Alliance is once again selling this equipment, although it is unsure how much profit it can yield given that they are now being produced by other organizations as well.
Name: Primus Keyarc Leather Pants

Description: Barghar equipment was born of an attempt to reproduce Ruklys' legendary magic resistance equipment. It may not be as effective as Ruklys', but it is fairly useful nonetheless.
Name: Primus Barghar Plate Pants

Description: The first person to ever wear this equipment was Geoffrey Parecius, grandfather of current Lancer Master Noer Parecius. He is said to have been close to the Black family, possessing a strong interest in equipment making himself as well.

Description: A strong piece of armor made with high-quality fabrics and magic fur. Very wearable and warm.

Description: A strong piece of armor made from an extremely rare type of white leather.

Description: A strong piece of armor made of a foreign metal name titanium. It is as heavy as it is tough.
Name: Primus Tajtanas Plate Pants

Description: A strong piece of armor made of an exquisite golden fabric. Rumor has it this armor was worn by the nobility in faraway nations.

Description: Long ago, when the goddesses crafted mystical objects for their amusement in the Goddess' Ancient Garden, some were crafted by coating existing ones with their divine power. These clothes are such examples.
Name: Ogva Robe

Description: It is unknown if the Goddess' Ancient Garden in which Ogva equipment was said to have been crafted indicates the same location that is known today or how long ago the events took place. However, it is widely believed that it took place before written history.
Name: Ogva Leather Tunic

Description: It is unknown how Ogva equipment were spread and revealed to the world. However, too much time has passed to find those origins.
Name: Ogva Chain Mail

Description: It was relatively easy to apply the magic derived from ferns that saw explosive growth after Medzio Diena to offensive equipment. There are cases where the effects changed or weakened in the case of protective equipment such as in the case of this outfit.
Name: Partis Robe

Description: The magic symbol Koru is hidden on this outift in the form of a fern sprout. Sprouts have long been symbols of great religious import.
Name: Partis Leather Tunic

Description: The magic extracted from ferns can be made to possess either light seeking or shunning characteristics. However, due to cost and practicality reasons, it is made to resist darkness even if it is theoretically possible to make it resist light.
Name: Partis Ring Mail

Description: Those that like to seek the stories related to magical items say that these robes were crafted when Tesla decided become a priest as well as an ordinary sculptor. The psychology of people whom like to attach mystical stories to Sirdgela equipment is a field worth researching.
Name: Sirdgela Robe

Description: Developments in the use of leather gained from wild animals that have always infested Sirdgela Forest are said to have been the origins behind this outfit.
Name: Sirdgela Leather Tunic

Description: It becomes evidence of an item being crafted long ago in a different environment if magical properties that are unrelated to the weather of a location is infused with equipment.
Name: Sirdgela Scale Mail

Description: This equipment, which used to be the full-dress uniform of the guards of the 3 layer castle wall, had special magical treatment for reasons only known by the leading members of the army. However, it seems that those reasons will be difficult to figure out as all the high ranking officers are dead.
Name: Philis Robe

Description: Unlike other pieces of Philis equipment, this piece did not exist before Medzio Diena. It was recently infused with magical properties out of necessity.
Name: Philis Leather Tunic

Description: This was equipment issued to guards, especially those that were in charge of attacking with fire on the 3 layer castle wall. An interesting theory that is brought up even now is that those guards may have been able to stop the catastrophic growth of vegetation from the capital which is now in ruins.
Name: Philis Scale Mail

Description: Some wizards tried but have failed to find if the new appearance of magical items in the Allerno region is due to the demons. Items that resist darkness such as this are proof that the theory is unlikely.
Name: Allerno Robe

Description: Another strange point about the magical items that have appeared in the Allerno region is that the mages that come here do not seek them. The items that are discovered are being used by residents or soldiers.
Name: Allerno Leather Tunic

Description: The lord of Allerno is trying to wear this equipment after enhancing it. It is said that he hired mages and craftsmen for this very reason.
Name: Allerno Plate Armor

Description: Many different kinds of experiments are enacted in order to craft Perelin items. The most widely known experiment was to have the pilgrims wear the equipment until divine power resides in it. The results indicate that this does not increase the chance of divine power indwelling in the equipment.
Name: Perelin Robe

Description: It is unknown why such phenomena occurs to pilgrims instead of pious priests that stay in one place. It is made even more unclear by the fact that there are certain cases proving otherwise. The most simple answer is that everything is done in the will of the goddesses.
Name: Perelin Leather Tunic

Description: According to legend, the first person to obtain Perelin equipment was the first Paladin master. However, it is unclear if this is the truth as the Tenet Church refuses to verify such trivial stories.
Name: Perelin Plate Armor

Description: Some Turn equipment is suspected to have been made by the same mage due to the similarities in their effects. As in the Turn pants and the Turn robe. But the possibility that they may have been crafted by different mages of different times can't be ruled out.
Name: Turn Robe

Description: There are several cases where they were created out of necessity of mages. It is said that Turn leather tunics were created on the spot to protect mages when conducting experiments with lightning.
Name: Turn Leather Tunic

Description: Metallic equipment was not made for centuries after Flurry's death because there was a shortage of metals thanks to the many experiments conducted by mages. As such, even though the existing metallic Turn equipment may have originated from mages, the actual craftsmen are anonymous people from outside the Mage Tower.
Name: Turn Plate Armor

Description: People being harassed by monsters after Medzio Diena require easily obtainable magical equipment. However, such support is not easy to receive due to several complications. The situation is bad enough that sometimes soldiers fighting monsters on the front lines are not able to obtain equipment they need. The fact that the Druid Master is using her power and resources for the Shaton region is a small but noble act.
Name: Shaton Robe

Description: The percentage of settlers in the Shaton region being burned while working has decreased dramatically after this outfit has been issued.
Name: Shaton Leather Tunic

Description: There are some of the belief that it is more important that people are protected from monsters even if they are abusing the Druid Master's goodwill. Such people praise the Druid Master for providing metallic armor.
Name: Shaton Plate Armor

Description: The reason why the Tyla Monastery receives particularly more contributions and donations is because it has historically been more lenient towards rulebreakers. The Tyla Monastery has treated sinners and lawbreakers alike gently focusing on reformation instead of punishment in accordance to the Monastery's traditions.

Description: A fine piece of armor made with high-quality fabrics and magic fur. Very wearable and warm.
Name: (Faded) Kalinis Robe

Description: A piece of armor made from an extremely rare type of white leather.
Name: (Faded) Albinosas Leather Armor

Description: A piece of armor made of a foreign metal name titanium. It is as heavy as it is tough.
Name: (Faded) Tajtanas Plate Armor

Description: A piece of armor made of an exquisite golden fabric. Rumor has it this armor was worn by the nobility in faraway nations.
Name: (Faded) Oksinis Robe

Description: A piece of armor made of monster leather and bones. Rumor has it warriors from faraway countries adorned their armor with large bones to represent their skill.
Name: (Faded) Kaulas Leather Armor

Description: A piece of armor worn by the royal knights of a faraway nation. It contains pure gold.
Name: (Faded) Krisius Plate Armor

Description: Once used as an alliance uniform in days of economic prosperity, today it is worn for slightly  different purposes.
Name: Alpra Robe

Description: A garment said to have originated from the East. Despite being made of leather, it is still a fairly breathable piece.
Name: Eastern Leather Armor

Description: As a piece of equipment made from layers of iron plate, it was initially specialized to resist arrow attacks. These days, however, it has evolved to protect against all types of attacks equally.
Name: Pangle Plate Armor

Description: A uniform worn by the kingdom's wizard combatants. Being able to wear this piece was considered a big honor in those days.
Name: War Mage Robe

Description: A uniform worn by the kingdom's rangers. In those days, rangers were treated with the same reverence as knights.
Name: Eaglestar Leather Armor

Description: The official uniform of the kingdom's knight order.
Name: Nyx Knight Armor

Description: Marone equipment originated from a religious order. In year 215 of the Kingdom, clerics began to divide into different orders, each developing their own style of equipment. Over time, these religious equipment items became more often used by those not related to an order.
Name: Marone Robe

Description: Prakeh equipment remains as a heritage from the era of King Chaspael. The lack of beauty in each item reflects the hardship of living in those times.
Name: Prakeh Robe

Description: Razna equipment is named after a species of monster currently extinct. According to legends, the last few were isolated in a special location, as they were considered dangerous by demons and goddesses alike. The association between this monster and the equipment it's named after remains a mystery.
Name: Razna Leather Armor

Description: Keyarc equipment was once once amongst the most popular items made by the Kedoran Alliance. After Medzio Diena, the Alliance is once again selling this equipment, although it is unsure how much profit it can yield given that they are now being produced by other organizations as well.
Name: Keyarc Leather Armor

Description: Barghar equipment was born of an attempt to reproduce Ruklys' legendary magic resistance equipment. It may not be as effective as Ruklys', but it is fairly useful nonetheless.
Name: Barghar Plate Armor

Description: The first person to ever wear this equipment was Geoffrey Parecius, grandfather of current Lancer Master Noer Parecius. He is said to have been close to the Black family, possessing a strong interest in equipment making himself as well.
Name: Suurit Plate Armor

Description: A strong piece of armor made with high-quality fabrics and magic fur. Very wearable and warm.
Name: Kalinis Robe

Description: A strong piece of armor made from an extremely rare type of white leather.
Name: Albinosas Leather Armor

Description: A strong piece of armor made of a foreign metal name titanium. It is as heavy as it is tough.
Name: Tajtanas Plate Armor

Description: A strong  piece of armor made of an exquisite golden fabric. Rumor has it this armor was worn by the nobility in faraway nations.
Name: Oksinis Robe

Description: A strong piece of armor made of monster leather and bones. Rumor has it warriors from faraway countries adorned their armor with large bones to represent their skill.
Name: Kaulas Leather Armor

Description: A strong piece of armor worn by the royal knights of a faraway nation. It contains pure gold.
Name: Krisius Plate Armor

Description: A top made using eagle feathers for flare. The feathers are not easily removed due to quality craftsmanship.
Name: Irellis Robe

Description: A top made from a special ivy. They are environmentally friendly.
Name: Jevenellis Leather Armor

Description: Made with overlapping plates. Due to this imbrication, moving around in it is quite comfortable.
Name: Basticle Plate Armor

Description: Among the old Nicopolis items that have reappeared after Medzio Diena, many are weapons, but armor items are relatively rare. There is no telling where the people who wore these items disappeared to, but some seem to have left behind their clothing.
Name: Planeta Robe

Description: Among the old Nicopolis items that have reappeared after Medzio Diena, many are weapons, but armor items are relatively rare. There is no telling where the people who wore these items disappeared to, but some seem to have left behind their clothing.

Description: Among the old Nicopolis items that have reappeared after Medzio Diena, many are weapons, but armor items are relatively rare. There is no telling where the people who wore these items disappeared to, but some seem to have left behind their clothing.
Name: Galaktikos Plate Armor

Description: The will of the Winterspoons came true. Thanks to this gear, many have survived and saw glory.
Name: Vine Armor

Description: This outfit is best suited for high-ranked clerics.
Name: Saint Robe

Description: After quickly discovering the weaknesses of the Plants, the Winterspoon family has openly been sharing ways to use this information with people.
Name: Plants Bracelet

Description: When inorganic matter mutates and becomes a monster, there is a way to weaken them by manipulating their spirits. This equipment contains a mechanism that does that.
Name: Control Bangle

Description: This bangle has been well known among hunters for a long time. With the sudden proliferation of monsters in recent times, more people are using it.
Name: Hunter Bangle

Description: The bloodthirsty instinct contained in one of its materials is said to impact the accuracy of the wearer.
Name: Bracer of Archer

Description: A very old recipe of which the time of origin cannot be determined. Although rare, it has been found in many diverse locations.
Name: Wizard Bracelet

Description: Originally from demons who passed the recipe down to the Vubbes, this recipe was released by human warriors who stole it from the Vubbes.
Name: Rapid Bangle

Description: There is a rumor that the price of jewels are about to skyrocket thanks to the increasing number of people who want to wear this.
Name: Glass Bracelet

Description: Goddess Jurate evicted demons living in the sea from her territory. As Merregina roams on the land, its purpose as material is becoming known.
Name: Merregina Bangle

Description: The study of strong demons and the creation of new magical weapons has become more important after Medzio Diena.
Name: Bearkaras Bracelet

Description: Its name reflects that the item is easy to get, not to imply that the item is shabby.
Name: Novice Bangle

Description: The origin of this bracelet is connecting to Lydia Schaffen and the Schaffenstar formed by her. However, there are no restrictions to use this bracelet for people who did not come from the Astral Tower.

Name: Anti-Dark Property Bracelet

Description: A bracelet which seems to be very effective at blocking Ice property damage. It is said to have been found occasionally deep inside the labyrinth.
Name: Anti-Cold Property Bracelet

Description: A bracelet which seems to be very effective at blocking ranged attacks. It is said to have been found occasionally deep inside the labyrinth.
Name: Kantravi Bracelet

Description: A bracelet which seems to be very effective at blocking unknown attacks. It is said to have been found occasionally deep inside the labyrinth.
Name: Tablet Bracelet

Description: The Fyrmes Bracelet symbolizes an eternal cycle, represented by the looped metal rings. It is also a reminder of the will of the goddesses to banish the demons and their chaos.
Name: Fyrmes Bracelet

Description: According to merchant rumors, the fact that this piece possesses a single stat is the fault of a beginner's mistake.
Name: Predji Bracelet

Description: This band was invented during the rule of King Kadumel when gladiator games were popular. With the increasing threat from monsters, this recipe is garnering attention.
Name: Gladiator Band

Name: Bracelet of Linne

Description: If you look closely, you can read an engraving: 'Crafted by the first humans, blessed by the origins of life when light and darkness existed equally'.

Description: During the Millenary 90 years ago, many items were crafted to celebrate the Great King Zachariel's founding of the kingdom. The items' necessity only increased after Medzio Diena.
Name: Zachariel Bangle

Description: Some avoid it due to the source of its power but such thoughts are considered a luxury after Medzio Diena.
Name: Abomination Bracelet
Set: {"$ID_NAME": "set_012", "Name": "Abomination Set", "Link_Items": [{"$ID": 603106, "Url": "equipment", "Name": "Abomination Bracelet", "Icon": "item_bracelet_03"}, {"$ID": 583105, "Url": "equipment", "Name": "Abomination Necklace", "Icon": "item_necklace_1"}], "$ID": 12, "Bonus3": null, "Bonus2": "All Stats {img green_up_arrow 16 16} 3", "Bonus5": null, "Bonus4": null, "Bonus7": null, "Bonus6": null}

Description: Created by mages to protect themselves from elemental magic, but due to a fatal flaw it couldn't be made.
Name: Elements Dance

Description: Among the efforts to combine holy and magic power while eliminating conflicting elements, a few objects were made that were both a success and a failure. This bracelet is an example of such paradoxical creations.
Name: Archmage Bangle

Description: A bracelet occasionally found in the labyrinth that has become very effective at blocking Dark property damage due to the various materials added to it.
Name: Rhevisan Bracelet

Description: The intense power of this bracelet is felt even before you wear it. Your enemies will feel it too as you attack.
Name: Smurto Bracelet

Description: Contrary to what rumors say, wearing this bracelet will not make you wiser. If you're a magic user and the wisdom you're looking for is attack power, that's a different story then.
Name: Ismintis Bracelet

Description: Hit ten times strong, and it's okay to miss once. That's what brave general Donahue thought.
Name: Stipiria Bracelet

Description: Designs like the one of this bracelet were popular around the time of the millenary. It was worn by gentlemen to attend banquets, although nowadays it is mostly a tradition among magic users.
Name: Svenus Bracelet

Description: Legends say this piece of equipment is made from the same material of the pipes used in demon buildings. Given the environmental differences between their realm and ours, it's hard to tell what conditions their pipes are made to endure. We can merely guess what characteristics this piece of equipment may possess.
Name: Worspej Bracelet

Description: After Medzio Diena, species of plants mutated into monsters, and combinations that were previously impossible became viable. For example, the combination of once-inanimate objects and materials obtained from existing monsters resulted in new kinds of equipment, the Symaere Bracelet being one of them.
Name: Viproti Bracelet

Description: The Basme Bracelet is said to originate from the demon realm and have a mind of its own. At any second the teeth that adorn it can come to life and attack its wearer.
Name: Basme Bracelet

Description: Rumor has it this piece of equipment was designed by Demon King Kartas. It is said that Kartas himself soon forgot about it, but his most ferocious subordinates started to produce it in large quantities until it infiltrated our world.
Name: Symaere Bracelet

Description: The Mejstra Bracelet symbolizes the life added to an eternal cycle. Many were the makers who devoted themselves to maintaining the symbolism in this piece.
Name: Mejstra Bracelet

Description: According to legends, the Svijes Bracelet was first created by a wizard known to have ventured into the realm of demons. After his body was discovered, the bracelet was the only way to confirm his identity.
Name: Svijes Bracelet

Description: It is unknown when or how this was crafted. It doesn't make one feel particularly nice due to its gloomy look.
Name: Dhrag Bracelet

Description: When the Atikha Bracelet was first produced, the process of joining the two semicircles that compose it was very important. Today the bracelet is made from a single piece, which makes it more dangerous but easier to craft even by inexperienced makers.
Name: Atikha Bracelet

Description: This piece represents the power obtained from allowing the voice of the goddesses to reach one's heart.
Name: Manosierdi Bracelet

Description: A common leather bracelet adorned with a flower trinket.
Name: Achiva Bracelet

Description: A bracelet decorated with colorful designs. The patterns were in fashion at the time the bracelet was created.
Name: Mirti Bracelet

Description: Originally a pearl bracelet, the central ornament was changed to produce different effetcs. Now, this bracelet's offensive properties are known to tire the wearer.
Name: Ufhor Pearl Bracelet

Description: This bracelet reflects the efforts of its makers to achieve a balanced performance through the use of a stable gem.
Name: Pik'o Pearl Bracelet

Description: A bracelet left behind by the Himil family at the time they separated from the Schaffenstar. The family later realized their mistake, but being in the possession of the bracelet's recipe, they did not demand to have it returned. It is said that the Schaffenstar themselves were unaware of the bracelet's whereabouts for a long time.
Name: Himil Legacy

Description: Lydia Schaffen used many accessories throughout her lifetime, some of which have since been divided and reconstructed. This bracelet is one of such accessories.
Name: Schaffen Bracelet Fragment

Description: Although they were rare, the Schaffenstar is known to have had its heretics, meaning those who wished to free themselves from the shadow of Lydia Schaffen. These people never managed to make much of an impact, but recently some of their remaining objects were put to use by Elder Adaux.
Name: Heretic's Bracelet

Bonus: [[59, 37.0], [51, -20.0], [66, "Triggers [Frenzy] for 5 seconds when an enemy avoids your attack"], [66, "Increases physical attack by {img green_up_arrow 16 16}235, movement speed by {img green_up_arrow 16 16}10 and reduces physical defense by {img red_down_arrow 16 16}88 for 30 seconds when stacking [Frenzy] 8 times"]]
Description: According to a legend, a warrior obtained this bracelet at the cost of relinquishing his sanity and humanity for pure frenzy, in order to seal away a very strong Demon King.
Name: Sissel Bracelet

Description: This piece of equipment will help you pierce through the demonic darkness.
Name: Lolopanther Bracelet

Description: This bracelet works by strenghtening the war spirit of those who wear it. It is very powerful, but it does not come without some drawbacks.
Name: Phada

Description: It is said that four Kupoles that served Goddess Zemyna had infused different kinds of magic into this piece of equipment.
Name: Solmiki Bracelet

Name: Akro Galia Bangle

Description: A bracelet made of mixed materials, said to improve mental clarity. Many of its wearers have experienced deeper states of meditation.
Name: Aiskus Bracelet

Description: Be careful not to injure yourself with the sharp metal parts. The identity of the owner of this bracelet remains unknown.
Name: Nepagristas Bracelet

Description: It was made with elegance for the Royal Palace and formal events while not being restrictive to the movements of your limbs.
Name: Highlander Costume

Description: Peltastas prefer a fancy outfit because they care more about flaunting their battle actions to their allies than the dangers of being spotted by an enemy.
Name: Peltasta Costume

Description: A costume made for versatile leg movement such as jumping and throwing a spear. Also appropriate for events requiring formal attire.
Name: Hoplite Costume

Description: The costumes have remained invariably faithful to tradition for the past thousand years.
Name: Centurion Costume

Description: Although Barbarians do not follow a particular style, this would be closest to their usual preference.
Name: Barbarian Costume

Description: Made to be appropriate for a horse rider. Also minimizes the burden to the mount.
Name: Cataphract Costume

Description: This costume consists of several layers of independent clothes. It demonstrates the wisdom of the seafarers.
Name: Corsair Costume

Description: It expresses their free spirit while maintaining the traditional look from the the Doppelsoeldners' place of origin.
Name: Doppelsoeldner Costume

Description: Made to weather any storm while also boasting defensive capabilities suitable for pitched battle.
Name: Rodelero Costume

Description: A traditional costume reflecting a Squire's requirement for clothing suited for long distance travel through various terrain.
Name: Squire Costume

Description: More than protection, the attire of a gladiator is first and foremost about showmanship. A perfect armor decreases the enjoyment of the audience, which is why the Murmillo's covers only half of the body.
Name: Murmillo Costume

Description: The cloth around the neck allows a Shinobi to cover their face when necessary. Doing so tells the adversary that they are a Shinobi without revealing their identity.
Name: Shinobi Costume

Description: Fencers require costly, high-quality garments, as even those of humble origins are connected with the higher classes through education or war. The Hutton family has long promoted the use of official uniforms for lower-class Fencers, which resulted in the extravagant fashions of traditional Fencer clothing being all but eliminated. This helped boost the status of lower-class Fencers, and it was the first step towards popularizing the occupation.
Name: Fencer Costume

Description: Dragoons, often descendants of nobility, tend to dress in a slightly ostentatious fashion. This, of course, does not diminish their ability in combat.
Name: Dragoon Costume

Description: Templars first started to wear the purple mantle as they began to separate themselves from the clergy by order of the empire. One could say the mantle is a symbol of royal authority over the church.
Name: Templar Costume

Description: Lancer garments are made with a type of metallic fabric that can maintain a good degree of malleability.
Name: Lancer Costume

Description: Although it is quite common, this Costume is worn by amateur Matadors who have limited experience dealing with beasts. There are some Matador also wear this to represent themselves as an expert in this particular field.
Name: Matador Costume

Description: Although it is quite common, this Costume is worn by amateur Matadors who have limited experience dealing with beasts. There are some Matador also wear this to represent themselves as an expert in this particular field.
Name: Matador Special Costume

Description: A Matador wearing this costume signifies that they have dealt with some of the most deadly beasts.
Name: Matador Belbeast Costume

Description: A Matador wearing this costume signifies that they have dealt with some of the most deadly beasts.
Name: Matador Belbeast Special Costume

Description: A costume only worn by veteran Matadors who are experienced with dealing with a large variety of beasts.
Name: Matador Bellanimal Costume

Description: A costume only worn by veteran Matadors who are experienced with dealing with a large variety of beasts.
Name: Matador Bellanimal Special Costume

Description: Tiro is the title given to rookie gladiators and as such, this outfit is given to those just starting their gladiator training.
Name: Retiarius Tiro Costume

Description: Tiro is the title given to rookie gladiators and as such, this outfit is given to those just starting their gladiator training.

Name: Nak Muay Costume

Description: Pyromancers believe their costume represents their image as both a wizard and a gentlemanly cleric.
Name: Pyromancer Costume

Description: Crafted to deal with extreme cold. Reflects the current master's personality which focuses on practicality.
Name: Cryomancer Costume

Description: Despite its neat look, the costume is very loose when worn. This is because Psychokinos hate being confined, whether it is their soul or their body.
Name: Psychokino Costume

Description: This multilayered costume is designed in such a way that it can be taken off layer by layer during an emergency.
Name: Alchemist Costume

Description: For a spellcaster robe, it is quite battle-optimized. If one thinks about the creatures they have to deal with, however, it's very much justified.
Name: Sorcerer Costume

Description: Due to their nature of pursuing connections among things, Linkers prefer a simple and plain outfit that will remind one of nothing at all. They say they do this so that people will not have a standardized view of Linkers.
Name: Linker Costume

Description: Chronomancers claim that their costume was Agailla Flurry's favorite style.
Name: Chronomancer Costume

Description: Although Necromancers themselves do not want to look sombre, their costume is dark enough to conduct a funeral.
Name: Necromancer Costume

Description: In truth, their costume does not match the magic they practice, but tradition is a very strong factor that cannot be ignored.
Name: Thaumaturge Costume

Description: It was crafted with careful consideration so as to not be identified with any particular branch of magic.
Name: Elementalist Costume

Description: Class garments are often adopted by the nobility for fashion purposes, regardless of their relation to the job. The same cannot be said for Sage clothing. Despite their trendy appearance, Sage clothes are produced with strong-smelling chemicals which, while helpful in keeping bookworms at bay, make the outfits unattractive to fashion-oriented folk.
Name: Sage Costume

Description: Warlocks may not be the most popular class in the social sphere, but their presence has long been customary at all kinds of gatherings. Because of this, Warlock garments are purposely made to look appropriate for balls and formal parties.
Name: Warlock Costume

Description: Featherfoots originate from outside the kingdom and research on them is scarce. Because of this, little is known about the elements of their clothing.
Name: Featherfoot Costume

Description: Despite their light appearance, Rune Caster garments are made to protect the wearer against the cold, while allowing for movement in warmer weather. This is a reflection of the climate in which Rune Caster clothing is produced.
Name: Rune Caster Costume

Description: Enchanters tend to value efficiency and performance over appearance, which is why their clothing is often simple and unadorned.
Name: Enchanter Costume

Name: Shadowmancer Costume

Description: This Costume is created in honor to the first Shadowmancer.

Description: A costume optimized and designed for long term survival in the forest.
Name: Hunter Costume

Description: It once used to be a uniform of the guards of a large city. However the costume remained the same even after Quarrel Shooters were long disassociated with such a role.
Name: Quarrel Shooter Costume

Description: The Ranger's costume is an evolutionary change of the Quarrel Shooter's costume.
Name: Ranger Costume

Description: Although Sappers are related to the Army, their outfit is unregulated due to their specialist role.
Name: Sapper Costume

Description: A very traditional costume from their hometown reflecting their history.
Name: Wugushi Costume

Description: This costume allows the wearer to freely turn their torso while mounted, and has been designed to be comfortable for the wearer's legs.
Name: Hackapell Costume

Description: A costume designed with a focused consideration on the time of activity rather than the environment.
Name: Scout Costume

Description: A solemn and valiant costume that gives reassurance and a trustworthy feeling to others.

Description: It offers a surprising defensive capability due to the thick fabrics used. Considering its wearer's role, mobility can be sacrificed without issue.
Name: Fletcher Costume

Description: Appraisers are known to be fond of comfortable clothing, although they tend to wear formal garments whenever they are required to contact with higher-class customers. This outfit is an example of that.
Name: Appraiser Costume

Description: The thick material of Falconer clothes is resistant to the hawk's claws, while also protecting them from damage.
Name: Falconer Costume

Description: Cannoneer outfits were originally similar to typical blacksmith clothing. With time, however, the class gained a higher status and its attire began to look more elegant.
Name: Cannoneer Costume

Description: Today's Musketeer garb is an exact replica of the royal honor guard uniforms worn centuries ago. Curiously, the honor guard now wears a modern version of those uniforms.
Name: Musketeer Costume

Description: The purpose of Mergen attire in its culture of origin continues to be unknown in the kingdom. So far, the Mergen Master has provided no clues to this mystery.
Name: Mergen Costume

Description: A costume given to every Bullet Marker that represents the dawn of days when firearms first came into use.
Name: Bullet Marker Costume

Description: A costume given to every Bullet Marker that represents the dawn of days when firearms first came into use.

Description: Priests believe they are the most neutral and traditional among the clerics and their costume reflects this belief.
Name: Priest Costume

Description: The Krivis proudly claim that they are the guardians of the oldest traditional faith. Their costume dates back to the Great King Zachariel's rule.
Name: Krivis Costume

Description: A costume fitting for any activity, whether it's for looking into a crystal ball, for knitting or for swinging a weapon.
Name: Bokor Costume

Description: The long drape used in this costume is said to be helpful for ourdoor living.
Name: Druid Costume

Description: This outfit was heavily influenced by the location of origin of its wearer.
Name: Sadhu Costume

Description: Needless to say, clothes uncomfortable for sculpting are not even considered.
Name: Dievdirbys Costume

Description: Soft and light, this costume is said to comfort and calm your body and soul.
Name: Oracle Costume

Description: A costume emphasizing the solemnity of a cleric while being comfortable enough for physical training.
Name: Monk Costume

Description: Like their suits, this costume gives a sense of faith to others.
Name: Pardoner Costume

Description: Paladins have two sets of costumes for different purpose: one for indoor prayer and another for outdoor battle. This one is for the latter.
Name: Paladin Costume

Description: Chaplain clothing combines colors and elements symbolizing the goddesses to convey a sense of security to battling soldiers. Despite this, the philosophy behind Chaplain garments does not allow for their adaptation to real combat situations.
Name: Chaplain Costume

Description: These garments are known to be highly resistant to dirt, allowing them to last for longer periods of time without washing. Not only that, they are designed for easy laundering.
Name: Plague Doctor Costume

Description: Traditionally, the ornaments in Kabbalist clothing each represent a different academic achievement. However, the lack of enforcement of this custom by the current Kabbalist Master has made it so that even beginners have started to wear the ornaments freely.
Name: Kabbalist Costume

Description: The Inquisitor's stole was originally worn only in occasions of judgement. Today, with the goddesses disappeared, it is worn at all times to help propagate the Inquisitors' doctrine.
Name: Inquisitor Costume

Description: Taoist garments are reminiscent of the style based in past academic traditions.
Name: Taoist Costume

Description: Miko clothing reflects the traditions of its culture of origin, resulting in a visible contrast with the local fashions of the kingdom. With the emerging status of Mikos in society, their style is also likely to influence future trends in the kingdom.

Description: Missio were gladiators who were given the right to leave the arena. Their specially designed shoulder guards were everlasting proof of their freedom.

Description: A special ornament given to Onmyoji to recognize their distinguished contributions after Medzio Diena.

Description: This item is a symbol of the Exorcist's faith. Those who carry the beacon on their backs have vowed to shine their light on the world even if they end up crucified. Story is told of a famous Exorcist who destroyed all demons within the vicinity of the beacon by allowing himself to be crucified. But, of course, there are few demons who will equal in power to an Exorcist who carries the beacon on their back.
Name: Vertex Beacon
